<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 17 at 3:48PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Blowing snow reducing visibility through the Madison River
Valley...
Southerly winds funneling through the Madison River Valley are
gusting in excess of 40 mph at times this afternoon, which is
causing loose snow to blow and drift through the area.
Visibilities of two miles or less are common, with some areas
going down to one mile or less. These conditions will likely
persist at least through this evening, making travel very
difficult.
Be aware that drifting snow will likely obscure potential icy
areas on the roadway. Drive with caution and be ready for changing
road and visibility conditions.</description>
